<br>
How?  Well, just make a new post, make the title of the post the name of your guild, and then in the body of your message, provide any information you wish.  That way, the posted of the message can edit his post and make changes as needed, and other folks can reply should the information change and the original poster no longer be available. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaudacitybarebottom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Audacity Barebottom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 500<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 2:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Free-form guild listing</span><hr size=1> sillyness <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ushylahsoulshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shylah Soulshine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/02 10:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Free-form guild listing</span><hr size=1> i miss the other list already <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uroddingham.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roddingham</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></s